  "prob_desc_output_spec": "Print a single number — the minimum required number of seconds. If Valera can't do the task in any time, print  - 1.",
  "source_code": "#include<stdio.h>\nint ara[200][2];\n\nint main()\n{\n    int n,i,j=1,x,f=0,sum=0,sumup=0;\n    scanf(\"%d\",&n);\n    for(i=0;i<n;i++)\n    {\n        scanf(\"%d %d\",&ara[i][0],&ara[i][1]);\n        sumup+=ara[i][0];\n        x=ara[i][0]+ara[i][1];\n        if(j&&(x&1))\n        {\n            j=0;\n            f=1;\n        }\n        sum+=x;\n    }\n    if(sum&1)\n        printf(\"-1\\n\");\n    else\n    {\n        if(!(sumup&1))\n            printf(\"0\\n\");\n        else\n        {\n            if(f)\n                printf(\"1\\n\");\n            else\n                printf(\"-1\\n\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    return 0;\n\n}\n",
